Auth/User Model Separation and Refactor Plan

This plan tracks the work to cleanly separate the auth system from the core user model, 
putting credentials and security in their own isolated domain.

## Objectives
- Isolate authentication logic from user profile management
- Introduce specific `auth_` tables for credentials, TOTP, and backup codes
- Update handlers, middleware, and services to use the separated model
- Complete data migration without dropping active sessions (where possible)

## Status
- Core backend migrations complete
- Auth package created and wired
- Frontend components updated
- Testing & validation ongoing

